pullRequest.title: Store OMRProcessorDesc in AOT Header
pullRequest.bodyText:
Previously we have TR_Processor and TR_ProcessorFeatureFlags in
AOT header. We will no longer be using TR_Processor and
TR_ProcessorFeatureFlags soon.
Issue: #9833
depends on: eclipse/omr#5197
Signed-off-by: Harry Yu harryyu1994@gmail.com

beforeCommit.message:
Switch from TR_Processor to OMRProcessorArchitecture in AOT Header

OMRProcessorArchitecture is the new processor types to use across
all platforms. It is an enum type defined in the OMR port library.
TR_Processor will be removed once all migrations to new cpu api's
are done. AOT Header is currently storing TR_Processor and we are
going to switch to OMRProcessorArchitecture.

Signed-off-by: Harry Yu <harryyu1994@gmail.com>

nodes.bodyText: This static means initialization happens only once. Is this going to have problems for JITServer (ARM is not supported yet, but maybe in the future)

Can you please put a comment for this piece of code? It's not clear to me the intent of the code.
It creates a new TR::CPU based on TR::Compiler->target.cpu which I thought it was a singleton.
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -183,6 +183,11 @@ J9::Compilation::Compilation(int32_t id,
 #endif /* defined(J9VM_OPT_JITSERVER) */
    _osrProhibitedOverRangeOfTrees(false)
    {
+   #if defined(J9VM_OPT_JITSERVER)
+      if (self()->getPersistentInfo()->getRemoteCompilationMode() == JITServer::SERVER)
+         _target.cpu = TR::CPU(TR::Compiler->target.cpu.getProcessorDescription());

nodes.bodyText: Do we have JITServer implementations on P and Z as well?
